comment: Evans (NOP) restricts Nelson's (DEN) FOM as he cuts across the lane, affecting his ability to catch the pass.
Evans (NOP) cleanly blocks the shot attempt of Nelson (DEN).
Faried (DEN) cleanly blocks the dunk attempt by Davis (NOP).
Barton (DEN) cleanly blocks Cunningham's (NOP) layup attempt before the ball makes contact with the backboard.
A timeout was requested and granted before contact occurs between Faried (DEN) and Evans (NOP).
Cunningham (NOP) grabs and pulls Gallinari (DEN), preventing him from rolling off the screen.
Nelson (DEN) establishes his left foot as his pivot foot, but moves it prior to the release of his dribble.
Faried (DEN) contests Davis's (NOP) jump shot, allowing him to land safely. He makes "hi-five" contact with Davis's hand after he releases the ball, which is legal.
LHH shows Faried (DEN) gathers the ball while stopping on his left foot, then crosses over with his right foot, then left, and then brings his right foot back to the floor before jumping off.
Davis (NOP) makes contact with the ball as he contests the layup attempt by Faried (DEN).
Faried (DEN) commits a take foul on Davis (NOP) prior to him starting his upward shooting motion.
Gallinari (DEN) sets the screen on Evans (NOP) and gives him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
Barton (DEN) follows Evans' (NOP) path on his drive to the basket, maintaining a legal guarding position.
Evans (NOP) makes contact with Lawson's (DEN) arm after he has released the shot, but the contact does not affect his ability to follow thru.
Gallinari (DEN) and Gordon (NOP) lock up momentarily away from the play and then release.
LATR shows Cunningham (NOP) follow Lawson's (DEN) path and then jump vertically in an attempt to defend the shot.
Gallinari (DEN) jumps vertically to contest Evans' (NOP) drive to the basket.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that the field goal made by Gordon (NOP) was released after time expired on the shot clock was upheld.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that the field goal made by Gordon (NOP) was released after time expired on the shot clock was upheld.
Faried (DEN) maintains legal guarding position while defending the drive to the basket by Davis (NOP).
Contact between Barton (DEN) and Evans (NOP) is initiated by Evans on offense, and incidental in his attempt to drive to the basket.
Gallinari (DEN) grabs and holds Davis (NOP) and restricts his FOM as he tries to cut away from the ball.
Faried (DEN) sets the screen on Cole (NOP) and gives him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
Cunningham (NOP) makes contact with Faried's (DEN) head as he contests the dunk attempt.
LHH and LATR Faried (DEN) and Davis (NOP) both go for loose ball, with incidental contact created in their attempt to reach it.
Barton (DEN) is in the paint and not actively guarding anyone for more than three seconds.
Evans (NOP) grabs Gallinari's (DEN) shorts, preventing him from rolling to the basket.
Cunningham (NOP) extends a forearm into Gallinari (DEN) above the free-throw line extended, which is an automatic foul.
LATR shows Evans (NOP) kick out his leg while turning, making contact with Gallinari's (DEN) leg while Gallinari is still in the air.
Evans (NOP) has two hands on the back of Gallinari (DEN) as he defends in the post, which is an automatic foul.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that the ball was last touched by NOP was confirmed and possession was awarded to DEN.
Gordon (NOP) maintains legal guarding position and cleanly strips the ball from Gallinari (DEN) on the drive to the basket.
Gallinari (DEN) draws Cunningham (NOP) into the air on the pump fake, and contact occurs while Gallinari has started his shooting motion.
Evans (NOP) commits a take foul on Barton (DEN).
